    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CRC calculation mismatch in PUSCH transport channel coding\n\n### Summary\nThe PUSCH transport channel coding was producing incorrect CRC values for 24-bit CRC calculations due to a bit positioning error in the SIMD-optimized CRC function. This caused UE devices to reject uplink transmissions with CRC errors.\n\nThe issue occurred because the `crc32_calc_pclmulqdq` function was returning 24-bit CRC results in the lower 24 bits of the 32-bit return value, while the calling code expected the CRC to be in the upper 24 bits to match the lookup table implementation behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/crc.h`: Modified `crc32_calc_pclmulqdq` return statement to left-shift result by 8 bits, placing the 24-bit CRC value in the upper 24 bits of the return value to match LUT implementation behavior.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder heavy uplink traffic conditions with multiple UEs transmitting PUSCH data, some UEs would consistently fail to receive uplink grants and report CRC errors. Packet captures showed correct payload data but mismatched CRC values compared to reference implementations. The issue was more pronounced on systems with SSE4.1 support where the optimized path was taken.\n\n"
}